properties.areaDesc: Flaming Gorge; East Sweetwater County; Rock Springs and Green River
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 4 at 2:45PM MST until February 7 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Watch for Sweetwater County Thursday through
Thursday Night...

...Strong winds aloft and a tight surface pressure gradient will
combine for high winds across Sweetwater County Thursday through
Thursday night...

* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Rock Springs and Green River, Flaming Gorge and East
Sweetwater County.

* WHEN...From Thursday through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation especially along Interstate
80. An enhanced blow over risk for light and high profile
vehicles including camper trailers and semi trucks.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Blowing snow will reduce visibility at
times, and created slick road surfaces.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
